."]}]},{"name":"Giles","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Much altered English vernacular form of the Late Latin name <i>Aegidius</i>, from Greek <i>Aigidios</i> (a derivative of <i>aigidion</i> ‘kid, young goat’), via Old French <i>Gide</i>. It was the name of an 8th‐century saint who, according to tradition, was an Athenian citizen who fled to Provence because he could not cope with the fame and adulation caused by his power to work miracles, in particular by healing the lame and crippled. This was not a particularly common name in the Middle Ages and its use seems to have been confined to certain families and localities."],"variants":[{"name":"Gyles","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Giles ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Giles Arden Knight was born in 1355, in Drayton, Warwickshire, England, his father, Giles de Arderne, was 11352 and his mother, Margaret Molineux, was 31. He had at least 2 daughters with Johanna Trillow. He died in 1375, in Drayton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 20."},"et":{"1355–1375":"1355–1375","1350–1381":"1350–1381","1372–1420":"1372–1420","1375–Female":"1375–Surnud","1330–1376":"1330–1376","1324–1382":"1324–1382","Abt 1372":"umbes 1372","circa 1375":"umbes 1375","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1376":"1376","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1330":"1330","1372":"1372","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","Drayton, Warwickshire, England":"Drayton, Warwickshire, England","Drayton, Oxfordshire, England":"Drayton, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1355–1375":"1355–1375","1350–1381":"1350–1381","1372–1420":"1372–1420","1375–Female":"1375–Kuollut","1330–1376":"1330–1376","1324–1382":"1324–1382","Abt 1372":"noin 1372","circa 1375":"noin 1375","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1376":"1376","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1330":"1330","1372":"1372","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","Drayton, Warwickshire, England":"Drayton, Warwick